#Text=Irbid
#Text=Irbid is a city in northern Jordan , some 88 km north of the capital Amman .
#Text=Understand

#Text=The main industrial and administrative centre in the north of the kingdom , Irbid is home to the Yarmouk University , the Jordan University of Science and Technology and a good range of services , making it a staging point for exploration further afield to Umm Qais ( Gadara ) , Pella and other nearby sites within the region .
#Text=Archaeological evidence reveals that Irbid has been settled since the Bronze Age .
#Text=During the Roman period , Irbid was known as Arabella .
#Text=The city 's ancient past now lies hidden beneath modern roads and buildings .
#Text=Get in
#Text=In Irbid , almost all means of road transportation arrive at .
#Text=Once there , you can hire a cab or local bus to anywhere in Irbid .
#Text=The is just south from here .
#Text=By bus
#Text=To get to Irbid you have to start out from ( Tabarbour ) Transport Terminal in Amman .
#Text=Buses to Irbid cost from 1 JD .
#Text=From the same terminal , the more comfortable coaches run by Hijazi Buses Co. cost 2.10 JD and are more direct as they do not stop between Amman and Irbid .
#Text=By taxi
#Text=Ordinary cabs , recognized by their yellow or beige colour , are more expensive .
#Text=But many of them have air conditioning , so they might be worth a try in the summertime .
#Text=Get around
#Text=You can get anywhere in Irbid by taking one of the many yellow or beige coloured taxi cabs .
#Text=Unlike in Amman , in Irbid it is rare for a taxi to use the meter , even if you insist .
#Text=Taxi rides in Irbid will typically be a set cost in increments of 0.5 JD , and you should negotiate the price before you depart .
#Text=You can also take a " service " taxi or a bus , which have scheduled routes and can drop you off on the way .
#Text=Ask the locals about the routes , because a ) there are no regular departure time tables , and b ) buses and taxi cabs wait up to take enough passengers in before taking off .
#Text=You should not pay more than 0.20 JD
#Text=See
#Text=There is not much to see in the town of Irbid , but from there you can go on and visit several ancient sites around the city .
#Text=Irbid Citadel ( right in the centre ) .
#Text=St. George Latin Church ( west of the citadel ) , ☏ +96227272314 .
#Text=Clock Tower ( south of the citadel ) .
#Text=Museum of Jordanian Heritage , Yarmouk University
#Text=( driving from Amman , turn left at the roundabout by the stadium , then right after 500 m ( around the stadium ) , and you will see an entrance about 500 m on the left , with a museum sign .
#Text=Check in with the officers at the gate and they will direct you to the museum , which is part of the University 's Institute of Archaeology and Anthropology . ) , ☏ +96227211111 .
#Text=Yarmouk University campus - considered by many the finest archeological museum in the country , designed in partnership with the German government .
#Text=Natural History Museum , Yarmouk University ( also inside the university , the museum is located in the green hangar #23 . ) .
#Text=winter/summer .
#Text=Exhibits
#Text=Jordanian fauna and flora .
#Text=Worth a visit .
#Text=Irbid Archaeological Museum ( Dar As-Saraya ) , Department of Antiquities building , Al-Ma'amun Street , ☏ +96227245613 .
#Text=Do
#Text=The town 's landmark thoroughfare is University Street , with restaurants , shops , and boutiques .
#Text=The street is also known for its myriad of internet cafes , for which reason Irbid boasts an appropriate entry in the Guinness Book of World Records .
#Text=Most cafes and coffee shops serve shisha ( hookah ) , for 1.50 JD .
#Text=There are many schools and colleges in the Irbid area , including Al-Yarmouk University and Jordan University of Science and Technology .
#Text=Students are mainly of Arabic background ; there are also many American and Malaysian students .
#Text=Buy
#Text=There are many shops in Irbid , especially on University Street and the streets nearby , selling souvenirs , jewelry , and clothing .
#Text=For international brands and souvenirs Amman is the better choice .
#Text=Eat
#Text=Try Al-Manqal , on University street , which serves decent grills and the usual Middle Eastern fare .
#Text=You can also try Arabella and Al-Saadi .
#Text=All of these serve the usual Middle Eastern grills , rice , hummus , and tabbulah .
#Text=They 're relatively cheap , especially for western visitors .
#Text=You will find all kinds of Arabic food to enjoy .
#Text=If you want to eat like the locals , buy felafel sandwiches or hummus from one of the numerous small delicatessen shops .
#Text=There are also many shawarma restaurants .
#Text=All of these are very cheap : Shawarma sandwich : 60 piasters ; felafel sandwich : 20 piasters ; hummus dish to go : 40 piasters .
#Text=Finally , McDonald 's is close to University Street Roundabout and Yarmouk University .
#Text=For fast food , there are also Quick Burger , Burger King , Pizza Hut , Popeye 's and other places , all on University Street .
#Text=If you 're looking for something in particular to eat , ask the local residents where you can find a food establishment that serves it .

#Text=Lukmeh Haniyyeh , Rateb Al Batayna Street , Across from Plateen Pharmacy ( when entering Irbid on the road from Amman ( Sharia’a Al Hus’n ) , drive until you reach the fourth traffic light ( at McDonald 's ) and turn right .

#Text=Continue straight and you will see the Irbid Chamber of Commerce on your right , and Lumeh Haniyyeh will be thirty meters beyond that on your left ( across the street from Plateen Pharmacy ) ) , ☏ +962799671611 , +962 775487959 .

#Text=Lukmeh Haniyyeh ( Delicious Bite ) serves up Jordanian classics ranging from a set menu of starters and mua’janat ( appetizer pastries ) and halouiat ( sweets ) to a rotating menu of daily specials such as maftool and maqlooba .
#Text=Even better , it serves a good cause .
#Text=The kitchen was started by Microfund for Women in partnership with USAID .
#Text=MFW took under-served women that previously made food products out of their homes , provided them with relevant trainings , and then gave them a kitchen .
#Text=The food is available to carry out , order by phone or eat in , and all proceeds support the financial empowerment of local women .
#Text=Starters : 0.10-1.50 JD .
#Text=Drink
#Text=There are no pubs or bars in Irbid .
#Text=You can , however , find numerous liquor stores in downtown Irbid .

#Text=These are mainly Christian-run enterprises , open to everyone , and they sell both domestic and international alcohol and beer , at reasonable prices ( although you should always ask about prices before buying ) .
